      "value": "What is Tree Shaking?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Tree shaking is a technique used to remove unused code from JavaScript bundles, reducing file size and improving performance."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Tree Shaking Matters"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Large JavaScript bundles slow down websites. Tree shaking ensures only the necessary code is included, improving load speed and efficiency."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Example"
    },
